<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8ee2e810-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290k–10"><num value="290k–10">§ 290k–10.</num><heading> Effectiveness of Convention</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Articles 43 through 48, inclusive, of the Convention shall have full force and effect in the United States, its territories and possessions, and the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, upon the entry into force of the Convention for the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8ee2e811-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/202/s101/e/tI">Pub. L. 100–202, § 101(e) [title I]</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1329-131">101 Stat. 1329–131</ref>, 1329–134.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8ee2e812-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8ee2e813-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id8ee2e814-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
